article.description: Chris Clemons had 32 points as Campbell beat South Carolina Upstate 82-66 on Saturday.
article.headline: Clemons scores 32 to lead Campbell over SC-Upstate 82-66
article.linkText: Clemons scores 32 to lead Campbell over SC-Upstate 82-66
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Chris Clemons had 32 points as Campbell beat South Carolina Upstate 82-66 on Saturday. Clemons made 12 of 14 foul shots. Ja'Cor Nelson had 18 points for Campbell (14-10, 7-3 Big South Conference). Andrew Eudy added seven assists. Malik Moore had 16 points and eight rebounds for the Spartans (6-20, 1-11). Campbell plays Hampton at home on Wednesday. South Carolina Upstate takes on UNC-Asheville at home on Wednesday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
